
A part of the College of Agricultural and Environmental Science of UC Davis, the Division of Textiles and Clothing offers the most comprehensive textiles and clothing and fiber and polymer science majors in the western United States, according to http://textiles.ucdavis.edu/ its official website.

Mission Statment: The mission of the Division of Textiles and Clothing is to develop and disseminate knowledge about the production, distribution and utilization of fibers, polymers and textile products. The strength and uniqueness of the program derive from an interdisciplinary perspective on commodityrelevant issues; we have a range of expertise from polymer science and textile technology to consumer psychology that allows us to take a systems approach to commoditybased problems.
